'''Shvash gas''' was a lower-quality and cheaper alternative for the gas used in the [[mini-flamer]]s used to light smoking material. It was often mixed with higher-quality gases to increase the pressure in a flamer's gas reserve.<ref name="PSG">''[[Platt's Starport Guide]]''</ref>

During the [[Cold War (Galactic Republic–Sith Empire)|Cold War]] between the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and [[Sith Empire (Post–Great Hyperspace War)|reconstituted Sith Empire]], the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]] [[Suudaa Nem'ro]] [[Mining/Legends|mined]] a pocket of shvash gas on [[Nal Hutta/Legends|Nal Hutta]]. [[Gender/Legends|His]] rival [[Voontara Fa'athra]] mined the same pocket out of an operation in the [[Rust Yards]], though Fa'athra could not refine it to the same degree Nem'ro did.<ref name="Subverting Karrels Javis">{{TORcite|type=class|Imperial Agent|Subverting Karrels Javis|Hutta}}</ref>

Shvash gas farming was a major industry on the planet [[Gelgelar/Legends|Gelgelar]], where it was used for heating and in cooking burners. On Gelgelar, farmers used pumps mounted on [[Repulsorlift/Legends|repulsor]] barges to collect the gas from the clouds over the swamps and the reserve pockets beneath the mud. Farmers on Gelgelar sold their pressure tanks of shvash gas to [[Vleen Argoe]] at the [[Shvash Gas Cooperative]] located at [[Gelgelar Free Port/Legends|Gelgelar Free Port]]. Vleen collected the gas into large tanks and sold them to freighter captains who transported the gas to mini-flamer companies such as [[Blycks]].<ref name="PSG" />

